ul, contingency fee lawyers must generate a portfolio of cases, similar to an investment portfolio with its associated risk. This has a significant impact on how contingency fee lawyers obtain and select cases, manage their work, and deal with the pressures that arise in settling cases. More important, understanding the work of contingency fee lawyers in terms of an ongoing practice rather than in terms of individual cases mitigates some of the significant conflicts that may exist between lawyers and clients.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 31. Jan 2022) 7aLAW / General Practice.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150362470240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503624702423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781503624702/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles